Text.Value: Onward. Let the words of Alaundo ring true.
Let's get this over with.
Fair enough.
The time has come. Ketheric will taste of death at last.
Seems like his prophecy missed a crucial part, though. Didn't say who gave the angel back her wings.
Very well. Side by side we'll stand as we'll rip True Souls from a false god. As good a prophecy as any.
I can't quite put my finger on why I trust you, but I do: the same instinct through which I know a wolf will bite, or allow itself to be petted.
Say no more. Just get the job done.
Let me prove it to you - join my party.
Well, that spared us all a tedious confrontation. We'll settle this by the sword.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) She dramatically draws her two scimitars in preparation for combat.

Text.Value: Ketheric is a formidable foe. I have need of a formidable ally.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChrisD] Soldiers raise their weapons while cheering
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) The assembled soldiers raise their weapons and cheer. Shouts of ‘Victory!’ resound.

Text.Value: So be it.
This is it then. The assault commences.
Say the word, and we're off.
I'm on your side if that's what you're insinuating. On the Harpers' side.
Keen eye. I suppose I could be persuaded.
A sound strategy. Once it's done, me and my Harpers will hold the ground floor while you hunt down the general himself.
That celestial being up there? I'm the one who freed her.
As long as we hold this floor, the tower is ours. I'll stay here - ensure no one comes up or down without a scimitar welcome.
Crazy old woman. You're talking to yourself.
If you're the last Harper standing, it's only fitting that you walk alone.
'Unshackled from shadows, she will rise in moonlit glory and carve a path of brightness to the accursed one's second death.'

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChrisD] Nightsong flies up and hovers over the moonrise tower
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) Jaheira looks up to where Nightsong is hovering over Moonrise Towers.

Text.Value: You'll bite. But not me. Not as long as we run in the same pack.
So sayeth the wise Alaundo.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) For this line she looks away from Nightsong and looks to us.

Text.Value: Foe it is. Strike them down.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) She dramatically draws her two scimitars in preparation for combat.

Text.Value: You're close now. A final audience with Ketheric Thorm awaits.
Let's do this.
So sayeth the wise Alaundo.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) For this line she looks away from Nightsong and looks to us with a mischievous smile.

Text.Value: That beacon of angelic wrath has taken the fight to Ketheric on the rooftop, and the first line of defence are dead.
Halt!
Godsspeed. You seem to be their chosen champion after all, against the false Absolute.
Foe.
The sword-point is the only one that matters now.
But storming the tower won't be easy, and if we wait too long, Ketheric will gather his strength and retaliate.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) When she says “You’ll have your hands full storming the tower”, she point towards the MT entrance where the enemy stands guard.

Text.Value: Later. We have enemies to silence first.
For now though, he's on the back foot for the first time since he returned from the grave.
Wish me luck.
I stand ready to reinforce, if you need it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Query - she's ready to fight if we need to recruit her
EditorData.logicalname: TOFIX - CHECK IF NEEDED / RETURNED TO RECRUIT

Text.Value: Good question.
At the ready, Harpers! In this light there will be victory! In this light we will avenge the fallen!
I am not a True Soul.
I'll hold this floor to ensure no one can escape the tower. You must press on, and find Ketheric Thorm.
This is it - the spearhead moment. You've brought us this far, so how shall we proceed?
Ready your weapons, Harpers. Be prepared to strike at my command.
'Unshackled from shadows, she will rise in moonlit glory and carve a path of brightness to the accursed one's second death.'

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) Jaheira looks up to where Nightsong is hovering over Moonrise Towers.

Text.Value: It would be my honour.
Onward. Let the hunt begin.
I'm Jaheira, and if our goals align, I may just be pleased to meet you.
I'm- I'm sorry you're alone. That Last Light went as it did.
Victory - and retribution.
Florrick left some of her Flaming Fist - they'll scout the prisons and barracks below, to ensure we're not taken by surprise.
Perhaps they don't. I care not. I care only for vengeance.
Wish me luck.
I detect a hint of envy. Perhaps you'd like to be there for that finale.
Halt!

EditorData.logicalname: CLEARED MAIN FLOOR - Has NOT Met (NOT HAV)

Text.Value: Baldur's Gate? Does that mean the Absolute has spread to the city as well?
Wrong answer.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) She dramatically draws her two scimitars in preparation for combat.

Text.Value: What criterion is it that would put me in either camp?
Must I stumble upon another nuisance every other mile? Out of my way, the lot of you!
Prove it.
Friend.
Actually, Jaheira, why don't you join me?
Likewise.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [ChrisD] Nightsong flies over the harpers soldiers
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) Gathered at the bridge that leads to Moonrise Towers stand Jaheira and her Harpers, flanked (potentially) by Counselor Florrick and her Flaming Fist soldiers. They’ve made it here through Nightsong’s corridor of light, while Nightsong herself flies dramatically over the tower.

Text.Value: Sounds like something my scimitars would say. They'll strike true. See to it you'll do the same.
It's all up to you now. Ketheric awaits.
A finale for the great Jaheira? I wouldn't miss it for the world.
I'm not in it for the glory. Victory is all that matters.
We move in and secure the ground floor first - cut off all exits.
You there, friend or foe?
My Harpers and I will be the noose that closes in around Ketheric, and as it tightens, you'll go in for the kill.
If you're hunting one target among many, the key is to isolate and corner it.
And mine.
You know the criterion exactly.
Lead on.
So I shall. Now let's run a hunt.
I'm touched. But I'm already spoken for.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) She nods towards the assembled Harpers.

Text.Value: Your Harpers are big boys and girls. They can handle themselves.
On second thought, it is rather vital that this floor remains secured.
Leave.
Believe me, I'm aching to have my revenge.
Better we fight separately.
Let's just concentrate on the fight ahead. The real battle has yet to begin.
Different packs then. As you wish. Just get the job done.
I reap every soul in this tower, until we are the last creatures standing.
Do what you will, just don't get in my way.
You fight well - with skill and purpose.
The time has come. Ketheric Thorm will taste of death at last.
You saw that celestial being flying over the tower, am I right? Well, I'm the one who freed her.
Actually, I'd rather you join my party, Jaheira.
I'm the last one standing, but I wouldn't be if it weren't for you. So what do you say? Shall we take the final steps together?
I don't need to prove myself to anyone. Now step aside.
Then consider yourself persuaded.
My Harpers are gone, shadows lost in the shadow theatre of my mind alone.
The words of a dead man mean nothing.
Leave.
Then consider yourself part of the pack.
So be it. See you on the other side.
All you need to know is that I'm here to kill Ketheric Thorm.
Let's circle this conversation back to some kind of point, shall we?
We can talk at length once the day is won - so let's win it first.
You don't say.
In that case we could find ourselves to be allies indeed. Me and my Harpers came all the way from Baldur's Gate to end the cult of the Absolute once and for all.
Truly?
You're the High Harper. You tell me.
May you strike like the viper and choke like the vine. Good luck.

Synopsis: Jaheira lead the harpers to Moonrise after Nightsong was freed. As the player arrives to Moonrise, she greets them and can follow the player for the assault, If she doesn't follow, she will still join combat and move into the tower, in which the player has another oppertunity to have her follow them to fight Ketheric. Once Ketheric flees she will move up to the roof to offer recruitment.
